Planigle is a Ruby on Rails based agile planning application. It was developed by and is copyrighted by
Walter Bodwell (2008).  It is licensed under GPLv2 (included in this distribution).

Required Components - License:
Ruby - Ruby (http://www.ruby-lang.org/en/downloads/)
Rails - MIT (http://www.rubyonrails.com/down)
MySQL - GPLv2 (http://dev.mysql.com/downloads/mysql/5.0.html)
HTTP Server - Apache (http://httpd.apache.org/download.cgi)
Flex - MPL

Embedded Components - License:
Ruby AMF (Rails Plugin) - MIT
Restful Authentication (Rails Plugin) - MIT
Cairngorm (Flex library) - BSD
Flex automation libraries - MPL (included for build convenience; part of Flex SDK)

Required Gems:
FunFX - MIT (from http://rubyforge.org/projects/funfx/)

Suggested Gems:
mysql (Ruby)

Suggested Eclipse plug-ins:
Aptana (http://update.aptana.com/update/3.2/)
  Note: This currently doesn't work with versions of RubyGems later than 0.9.4.
Subversion (http://subclipse.tigris.org/update_1.2.x)
Flex Builder (See http://www.adobe.com/cfusion/tdrc/index.cfm?product=flex_eclipse&loc=en_us)
  Note: There is a 60 day free trial, but this costs money if you chose to use it
SQL Explorer (http://eclipsesql.sourceforge.net/)
  Note: You can get the MySQL JDBC driver from http://dev.mysql.com/downloads/connector/j/5.0.html
  
See Installation_notes.rtf for help on getting your environment up and running.

Testing Note: To get the Flex integration tests working, you'll need to do a test build (rake build:test).
You'll also need to have a separate process running on the same box configured as a test environment
when you run the tests.  Then run the rake test:flex task.